  "market_context": "Light Crude Oil Futures (CL1!) on January 30, 2024. Price had been declining, creating multiple equal lows (sell-side liquidity) below. London session formed a low that initially appeared to be a reversal, but no higher time frame PD array was engaged.",
  "key_observation": "London formed a low that looked like a London Reversal, but price never reached a higher time frame PD array. This created a fake change in state of delivery. New York open then made an opposing run lower, sweeping the sell-side liquidity, before reversing aggressively higher through stacked failure swing highs (low resistance liquidity).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified that London session formed a low, which initially appeared to signal a London Reversal to the upside.",
    "Step 2: Checked to the left for a higher time frame PD array — confirmed price never reached one, invalidating the London Reversal classification.",
    "Step 3: Noted that the London low was only creating more equal lows / additional sell-side liquidity rather than engaging a meaningful HTF level.",
    "Step 4: Recognized this as a fake change in state of delivery on the M15, anticipating a further run lower into New York open times.",
    "Step 5: Looked left and identified multiple failure swings forming stacked equal highs (buy-side liquidity / low resistance liquidity) above current price.",
    "Step 6: Dropped to a lower time frame (5-minute) to monitor price action around the New York open (8:30 EST).",
    "Step 7: Observed New York open make the opposing move lower, sweeping the sell-side liquidity lows; price attempted to close below but failed.",
    "Step 8: Identified the New York open candle as the order block — waited for a close above it to confirm the change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 9: Entered long on the close above the NY open order block, placed stop below the swept low.",
    "Step 10: Targeted the stacked failure swing highs (London and Asia session highs) as take-profit levels, with partials at midnight open and continuation through the highs — confirmed as a New York Reversal profile."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long trade triggered at New York open order block close-above. Price ran through midnight open and through the London/Asia failure swing highs. High R-multiple trade; partials taken at midnight open and at the stacked highs. Confirmed New York Reversal daily profile.",
  "lessons": "If London forms a low but never engages a higher time frame PD array, it is a fake change in state of delivery. Expect New York to make the true liquidity sweep lower before reversing. Stacked failure swing highs above provide low resistance liquidity for an aggressive move once the real reversal is confirmed.",
